# binomial distribution is a discrete probability distribution that describes the number of successes in a fixed number of independent Bernoulli trials. it is defined by two parameters: the number of trials (n) and the probability of success (p). the binomial distribution is used to model situations where there are only two possible outcomes (success or failure) and the trials are independent. the binomial distribution can be used to calculate the probability of getting a certain number of successes in a given number of trials.